  "texts": [
    "Our analysis suggests that CLEAR outperforms chunk embedding and full-note approaches for two main reasons.",
    "First, CLEAR retrieves shorter context segments.",
    "Prior studies have shown that longer contexts can degrade LLM performance.",
    "For example, in the FlenQA dataset, which involves three reasoning tasks, Levy et al.",
    "observed that as input length increases, model performance deteriorates regardless of whether the key information is located at the beginning, middle, or end of the input context, and that degradation occurs well before reaching the context limit of the models 42."
